Value.value: Not bad finding your way here, but we're going to need to know just how discrete you really are.
All's we're asking for is a simple delivery. Head to Demonreach, look for Pritchard for the goods.
Pritch'll give you a replica. We'll need you to swap it for the real deal in the warehouse in Southport West. Look for crate numbered 541893.
After you do it, take it to Kampo's. A woman named Merey should be waiting by the bar.
Nice work. Here's a bit of a bonus. If you can find her, one of our mages, Bess, is looking for someone to do some work.
Simple enough. You can get to Demonreach by way of Central or Kampo's.
Look for Bess. You'll have to go deeper into the tunnels to find her though.

value.0: Quick of spell and keen of mind, these mages weren't trained in any formal academy. But don't expect that makes them any less dangerous.
This is a settlement guard insignia for the guard templates.

Value.value: Well, well, well. Gregor sends his recommendation, does he? We'll see what you're really worth.
There's a defector to the guild that's gotten a bit... mouthy. I hear tell she's planning to talk to the guard.
Do what you gotta do to keep 'em quiet. You know what I'm saying?
She's a tinker, so she might have tricks against sneaking. Get creative.
She's holed up in House Amorzi's summer home in Central. I got a copy of the key right behind me. Pfeh. Bring back her ring when the job's done.
Nice work. I'm actually impressed! Take this. It'll mark you as one of our own.
I don't see no ring on you. Get to it. House is just off the market in Central. And grab the key.
You did good. Real good. Go on inside.
Get lost. I don't speak to no one who ain't vetted.

This cloak is an intricate weaving of hearty forest leaves, created in the forest grove by a circle of rangers and druids.  It emanates the very life force of the forest itself, healing the bearer's wounds as they appear.  In the hands of a ranger, this accessory becomes a valuable tool, aiding in most of her abilities in some way or another.

If ever there were a bow to signify a person's standing in a wood, it'd be this bow. The bow itself has been lovingly carved from only the finest material. A permanent Ironwood spell and a fine bowstring ensure any arrow notched in this bow will fly quite true.

Additionally, many druid spells have been cast on this bow allowing it to boost the wielder's ability to see her enemy. Only ones familiar and understanding about nature may pluck the bowstring, others will snap it.

Value.value: What's the word? You got a job or not?

These throwing knives have been soaked in a concentrated poison vat; so much so that the poison has soaked into the metal. Instantly crippling, these throwing knives flow into the air on being thrown, and on contact release its venom into the target's bloodstream.

Known effects of being hit by such knives include numbness, muscle tissue melting, organs shutting down and a number of other unpleasentries.

There was once a priest who saved many patients from sickness and death. Word of his skills spread, and so great did his renown grow that he was appointed healer to the king.

Several years passed. One day, the king's daughter fell gravely ill. Despite all the doctor's skill and efforts, the illness proved fatal, and the princess slipped into death.

A hateful grudge toward the doctor took root in the grieving king's heart. Deaf to the priest's entreaties, the king sentenced the healer's family to death.

Mad with grief, the doctor threw deadly poison in the royal well, and the entire royal household died agonizing deaths. The blade of this axe was sharpened using water drawn from that well.
